<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1017332-i-ve-read-dreams-of-ada-any-reason-to">I&#39;ve read Dreams of Ada. Any reason to read this too? I know it&#39;s a different case but is it still basically the same. Also does anyone have a good recommendation of a true crime book that takes place in Louisiana preferably New Orleans</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1017332'><a id="like_count_community_question_1017332" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/1017332?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">1 like</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F5345.The_Innocent_Man">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/1017332-i-ve-read-dreams-of-ada-any-reason-to">4 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1017332-i-ve-read-dreams-of-ada-any-reason-to">See all 3 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/5443870-carla"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1343863996i/5443870._UX100_CR0,10,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/5443870-carla">Carla</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">The Innocent an follows a different murder than The Dreams of Ada. The Dreams of Ada case is referenced and described in the book, but those men are s<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">The Innocent an follows a different murder than The Dreams of Ada. The Dreams of Ada case is referenced and described in the book, but those men are still in prison. The Innocent Man describes 2 different men that were convicted of a different murder in Ada, and have been exonerated. Therefore, Yes - there is a reason to read this book in addition to The Dreams of Ada.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
