<div id="review_11158474" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/11158474" />
    <a title="Daniel Perlman" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/58837243-daniel-perlman"><img alt="Daniel Perlman" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1606171551p2/58837243.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/11158474?book_show_action=true">Dec 28, 2007</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Daniel Perlman" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Daniel Perlman" href="/user/show/58837243-daniel-perlman">Daniel Perlman</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780440243830" href="/book/show/397229.The_Innocent_Man">review of another edition</a>

          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">The World!</span></div>

        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer11158474" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17055316978269048013">I&apos;ve enjoyed a few Grisham&apos;s in my day, and of course seen a few of the films... But this book is stunning, and it&apos;s his first non-fiction.<br/><br/>I myself practice criminal law, and of course if you asked me, I&apos;d say there are bad cops out there, and bad prosecutors, and bad defense attorneys and bad judges, but I would not have imagined the devastating travesty that unfolds on these pages.<br/><br/>This is a story of small town justice going way south. It wasn&apos;t vigilante but it wasn&apos;t far off. They used the &quot;s</span>
  <span id="freeText17055316978269048013" style="display:none">I've enjoyed a few Grisham's in my day, and of course seen a few of the films... But this book is stunning, and it's his first non-fiction.<br /><br />I myself practice criminal law, and of course if you asked me, I'd say there are bad cops out there, and bad prosecutors, and bad defense attorneys and bad judges, but I would not have imagined the devastating travesty that unfolds on these pages.<br /><br />This is a story of small town justice going way south. It wasn't vigilante but it wasn't far off. They used the "system" over two decades to accomplish what a mob and noose once accomplished overnight.<br /><br />The evil that even prosperous, educated people can do to one another is astonishing in this detailed, chilling account of a man who's constitutional rights are run roughshod over en route to a death penalty conviction for a murder he did not commit and for which no real evidence existed.<br /><br />This is an informative, exciting, fast paced, real life chiller that everyone should read to understand how something unbelievable can and apparently does happen to "anyone."</span>
  <a data-text-id="17055316978269048013" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

